[With 800 cattle dead of rabies in the region since the beginning of the
year, this cannot be regarded as anything but a serious situation.
Vaccination and vampire bat control are well proven techniques for
controlling bovine rabies in Latin America if pursued actively. The usual
technique for controlling vampire bats is to smear captured bats with
poisons, my memory says it was anticoagulants, which through mutual
grooming get dispersed in the bat colony on the bat's release. From the
numbers dead I suspect that the situation began well before the end of last
year. There are a number of vampire bat species involved in rabies and with
different roosting habits. In my experience in Brazil, vampire bat rabies
would break out in cattle some two to three years after forest & woodland
clearances because the bats no longer had sufficient animals to feed on in
the forest and were forced to search outside, which brought them to feed on
the cattle. - MHJ
